{"article_id":"lPj3lxV0bzwoHZAC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The U.S. economy added a record 4.8 million jobs in June ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"according to federal data","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"released Thursday ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"but a surge in new infections and a spate of new closings threatens the nascent recovery .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Two key federal measurements showed the precarious place","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"the economy finds itself in three and a half months into the pandemic","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"as the country struggles to hire back the more than 20 million workers","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"who lost their jobs in March and April .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"While companies have continued to reopen ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"a large number of Americans are finding","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"their jobs are no longer available .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"The unemployment rate in June was 11.1 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics said ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"down from a peak of 14.7 percent in April but still far above the 3.5 percent level","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"notched in February .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"And another 1.4 million Americans applied for unemployment insurance for the first time last week","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and more than 19 million people are still receiving unemployment benefits , stubbornly high levels","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that show","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"how many people are struggling to find or keep work .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"The Congressional Budget Office on Thursday said","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"the coronavirus pandemic gave such a shock to the labor market","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"that it would not fully recover for more than 10 years .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"President Trump touted the jobs","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that were added at a news conference","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"called shortly after they were released ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"they were a sign","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"that \" America ' s economy is now roaring back to life","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"like nobody has ever seen before . \"","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"\" All of this incredible news is the result of historic actions","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"my administration has taken , \"","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Trump said .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"But his top aides acknowledged","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"there was still a long way to go .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"\" There is still a lot of hardship , and a lot of heartbreak , in these numbers , \"","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow said .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"\" I think","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"we have a lot more work to do . \"","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"The stock market initially rose on the news ,","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"with the Dow Jones industrial average rising 400 points , or 1.5 percent ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"before retreating .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"It closed up 92 points on the day .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"Economists called the 4.8 million jobs added encouraging ,","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"they were a sign","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that the massive financial incentives","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"that Congress passed","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"appeared to have succeeded","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"at stanching even greater job loss .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"But the good news came with a couple of significant asterisks :","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"It was gathered the week of June 12 ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"when the country was reporting less than 25,000 new cases a day , not the current average of more than 40,000","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that has sent new closures and shutdowns cascading across states and counties .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"\" The pandemic pushed us into a very deep economic hole , \"","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"said Mark Zandi , chief economist at Moody ' s Analytics .","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"\" We can certainly fall back . \"","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"The more than 14.7 million people","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"who are still out of work","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"have left the country with an unemployment rate higher than any point during the Great Recession .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"The unemployment insurance data ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"based on statewide claims","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"that are separate from the survey","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"that informs the jobs report ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"paints an even less sanguine picture :","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"Last week was the 15th straight","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"where unemployment claims exceeded 1 million , a sign","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that the economic recovery has not taken hold for many Americans .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"The strong month of job gains was driven by robust hiring in the leisure and hospitality sector ,","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"with 2.1 million additional jobs added ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"accounting for about 40 percent of the total","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"gained for the month .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Food services and drinking establishments saw their payrolls swell by 1.5 million people ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"but they still remain 3.1 million lower than before the pandemic .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"These are the industries","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"that are getting hit hard in the past two weeks by new closings ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"as a numbers of states shuttered bars and restricted restaurant service","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"as they try to get the case surge under control .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Retail gained back 740,000 jobs ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"though employment remains at less than half its pre-pandemic level ;","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"education and health services regained 568,000 jobs","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"and health care 358,000","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"as people returned to the offices of dentists , physicians and other medical practitioners .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"The data bring into sharper focus the turmoil","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"facing the U.S. economy","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"after many businesses sent workers home in March during the beginning of the spike in deaths","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"caused by the virus .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Many companies began rehiring in May and June ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"but there are signs","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"that some workers are getting laid off for the second time in just a few months .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"Gabriel Erales , 39 , the executive chef of Comedor in Austin , Tex. , described","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"how the food service industry has been caught in this rapid shift .","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"The restaurant pivoted to be a home-meal preparation service in March ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"reducing its staff by about 60 percent for months ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"before reengineering its dining room","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"to reopen for service .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Reservations picked back up after the June 18th reopening ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"but Erales said","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"there are signs","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"that they are on the wane again","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"as the case load surges .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"\" It ' s very unpredictable , \"","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"\" At this point we really have no outlook","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"on what business could be . \"","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"Many Americans remain employed","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"but are working drastically reduced schedules","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"- more than 9 million workers reported working part time","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"because of economic reasons ,","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"more than double the level in February before the pandemic .","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"Still a participation rate of 61.5 percent in June , slightly up from April and May but nearly a percentage point below February , indicates","depth":5},{"id":110,"text":"that others may be leaving the labor force all together","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"- an echo of the deep economic turbulence in the Great Recession .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"Economists said","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"there are other reasons","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"to be concerned","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"as incentives","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"for businesses","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"to retain employees","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"and some benefits","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"that have allowed people out of work to stay afloat financially","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"are winding down","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"without more federal action .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"Federal and state officials struggled to time their reopening efforts in April and May ,","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"in some cases ignoring warnings from public health officials .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"Now , cases in some of the states","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"that reopened the fastest , or with the loosest restrictions ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"are seeing the biggest spikes , such as Florida , Arizona and South Carolina .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"In recent days , Texas shut down all bars","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"just weeks after they had reopened .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"California announced the closure of bars and indoor dining in 19 counties , more than 70 percent of the state .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"And at least nine other states have slowed or reversed their reopenings .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Restaurant bookings have begun to sink in hard-hit states such as Florida , Texas and Arizona .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"Job postings on the Indeed website , though up from a low of 39 percent , are still down 24 percent from last year .","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"Many workers are starting to report","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"being laid off or furloughed for a second time in just a few months .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"But those effects will not be captured in these reports for the most part .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"In the May jobs report , there was a particular focus on a misclassification error","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics said","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"it made","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"that marred how it calculated the unemployment rate .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"On Thursday , it said","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that issue had been mostly fixed .","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"The BLS said","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"the true unemployment rate is probably closer to 12.1 percent , one percentage point higher than the official rate","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"it gave .","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"Last month ,","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"it said","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"the unemployment rate was 13.3 percent ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"but the data collection error had artificially lowered it from 16.3 percent .","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"In April , the 14.7 percent official rate was likely closer to 19.7 percent .","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"The disconnect stems from the way","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"surveyors interview people about their job status ,","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"as many Americans are unclear about whether they have actually been laid off or just sent home temporarily .","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"There are other strains on the economy .","depth":4},{"id":154,"text":"Only a third of the 22 million Americans","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"who lost their jobs in March and April","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"have returned to work so far .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"The number of people","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"who reported","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"permanently losing a job","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"rose by 588,000 in June ,","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"bringing the total since February to 2.9 million","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"\" It ' s becoming clearer that some of what","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"people hoped","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"were temporary layoffs","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"are now turning into permanent layoffs , \"","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"said Donald Marron , an economist at the Urban Institute .","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"The new unemployment claims , a different measurement","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"which has stagnated between 1.4-to 1.5 million a week during the last month ,","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"remain at more than double the pre-pandemic record ,","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"pointing to the magnitude of the crisis .","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"With the supplemental insurance","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"given to gig and self-employed workers ,","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"that number was well over 2 million last week .","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"\" I would take solace with these numbers","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"but I wouldn ' t pop any champagne , \"","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"Zandi said .","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"\" It ' s 10 times what you would see in a well-functioning economy . \"","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"At the start of the pandemic , most workers believed","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"they would quickly be rehired ,","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"but","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"as the deadly virus continues to be a danger ,","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"more and more businesses are telling workers","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"they will never get their old job back .","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"The job loss has had a disproportionate affect on people of color as well .","depth":7},{"id":185,"text":"The jobless rate for black people is 15.4 percent and 13.8 percent for Asians .","depth":8},{"id":186,"text":"For Latinos , the jobless rate is 14.5 percent .","depth":8},{"id":187,"text":"Federal legislators continue to wrangle over proposals","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"that would continue or extend some of the emergency unemployment benefits","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"that will run out by the end of July .","depth":8},{"id":190,"text":"Democrats and the White House are at odds over how to authorize the funds","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"even though there are large numbers of people still out of work .","depth":8},{"id":192,"text":"White House officials told outside advisers on Thursday","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"that the jobs report makes it less likely","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"they will approve legislation","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"that would cost as much as $ 2 trillion or $ 3 trillion ,","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"according to Stephen Moore , a conservative close to the White House .","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"Moore said","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"the jobs report is also likely to shore up White House opposition","depth":12},{"id":199,"text":"to extending the significant increase in unemployment benefits","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"approved by Congress in March .","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"\" There will be a Phase 4 ,","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"but this makes the case in their eyes for a smaller one","depth":14},{"id":203,"text":"and makes even stronger the case","depth":15},{"id":204,"text":"for not extending the unemployment benefits , \"","depth":15},{"id":205,"text":"Moore said .","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"\" You don ' t have the sense of crisis","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"you did a few weeks ago . \"","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"Trump and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin on Thursday talked about providing more money for businesses and schools ,","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"but Mnuchin said","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"they had not decided on what to do for households .","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"\" Our work is not done","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"until every single American","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"who lost a job","depth":14},{"id":214,"text":"because of covid","depth":14},{"id":215,"text":"is back to work , \"","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"Mnuchin said .","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"[ Are you newly unemployed or concerned about safety","depth":7},{"id":218,"text":"as you head back to work ?","depth":7},{"id":219,"text":"We would like to hear about your experiences . ]","depth":6},{"id":220,"text":"There are some positive indications about the country ' s reopening .","depth":5},{"id":221,"text":"Data","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"gathered by the HR software company Kronos on 30,000 private industry businesses and 3.2 million hourly workers","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"found","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"that businesses had by the end of last week recovered more than half","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"- 59 percent -","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"of the work shifts","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"they lost between March and April .","depth":11},{"id":228,"text":"Even in places","depth":10},{"id":229,"text":"where coronavirus cases are still surging ,","depth":10},{"id":230,"text":"more workers clocked in in the last week of June than at the beginning of the month .","depth":9},{"id":231,"text":"\" From February through June , we will have seen an enormous amount of job loss , \"","depth":8},{"id":232,"text":"Jason Furman , a former top economic adviser to President Barack Obama , said on a conference call","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"organized by Rep. James E. Clyburn","depth":11},{"id":234,"text":"( D-S.C. ) ,","depth":11},{"id":235,"text":"the chairman of the House ' s coronavirus subcommittee .","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"\" Whatever happens month to month ,","depth":7},{"id":237,"text":"the economy is in a much worse place","depth":8},{"id":238,"text":"than it was four months ago . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":477,"left":342,"right":476,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":342,"left":276,"right":341,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":260,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":257,"right":259,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":242,"right":256,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":241,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":241,"left":0,"right":240,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":248,"right":255,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":245,"right":247,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":245,"left":243,"right":244,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":243,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":8,"right":246,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":246,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":255,"left":251,"right":254,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":251,"left":249,"right":250,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":249,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":15,"right":253,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":253,"left":16,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":252,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"attr